50|$|NTBackup is the {{built-in}} backup application introduced in Windows NT around 1997 {{and part of}} all subsequent versions {{up to and including}} Windows 2000, Windows XP and Windows Server 2003. It uses a proprietary backup format (BKF) to back up files. Files can be backed up to tape, <b>ZIP</b> <b>drives,</b> floppy disks, and hard drives. It also features integration with Task Scheduler and has several command line switches for scheduled automated backups.|$|R
